## 🛠️ Components Used
- Solar Panel  
- DC Motor (Grass Cutting Blade)  
- Battery (Energy Storage)  
- Sun Tracking Sensors (LDR / Light Sensors)  
- Servo Motors (Panel Movement Control)  
- Microcontroller (Arduino / ESP32 based control system)  
- Motor Driver Circuit  

---

## ⚙️ Working Principle
The system uses light sensors to detect sunlight intensity and direction. Based on the sensor inputs, the microcontroller controls servo motors to align the solar panel toward maximum sunlight.

The solar energy is stored in a battery and used to power the DC motor connected to the grass cutting blades. This ensures continuous operation with minimal manual intervention while maximizing energy efficiency through sun tracking.

---

## 🔄 System Architecture
Sunlight → LDR Sensors → Microcontroller → Servo Motors (Sun Tracking)
↓
Solar Panel Alignment
↓
Battery Charging System
↓
DC Motor (Grass Cutter)

